The application requires a PostgreSQL installation (>=9.4) with a 
database named  toucan . Configure the database connection by extending 
the  DATABASES  object in  issues_tracker/settings/__init__.py :  DATABASES = {
  'default': {
    'ENGINE': 'django.contrib.gis.db.backends.postgis',
    'NAME': 'toucan',
    'USER': 'postgres',
    'PASSWORD': 'postgres',
    'HOST': 'localhost',
    'PORT': 5434
  }
}  To create the database scheme run the migrations (this might require 
PostgreSQL superuser rights to install the postgis extension):  ./manage.py migrate
